CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 16, 1962, pg. 23 reads: "Tabulating Scores - Members of the Alpha Wives are busily tabulating the scores of players at their annual bridge luncheon, which took place Saturday at Hotel Webster Hall.  Left to right, seated: Mmes. Franklin E. Bolden, George W. Little, Wendell G. Freeland, Frederick S. Humphries, LeRoy Patrick, Wilbur C. Douglass Sr. and Robert L. Vann.  Standing; Mmes, Larry Green, John Cundieff, Lawrence Moncrief, Richard S. Bennett, Wilbur Douglass Jr., Edward Hale, Robert Lawson, James Miller and John Walker. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of four women, including woman wearing sleeveless dress with embroidered bodice and headband, seated at card table playing bridge, in Webster Hall for Alpha Wives annual bridge luncheon
